---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy - CoreShot">
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-[#0F172A] pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <article class="prose prose-invert prose-red max-w-none">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2">CoreShot Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-[#9CA3AF] mb-8">
          <strong>Effective Date: November 5, 2025</strong><br>
          <strong>Last Updated: November 5, 2025</strong>
        </p>

        <hr class="border-white/10 my-8">

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">1. Data Controller</h2>
          <p class="text-[#E5E7EB]">The controller of your personal data is:</p>
          <p class="text-[#E5E7EB]">
            <strong>CoreShot Sp. z o.o.</strong><br>
            VAT: [INSERT VAT] | Company No: [INSERT REGON]<br>
            email: <a href="mailto:privacy@coreshot.eu" class="text-[#E11D48] hover:underline">privacy@coreshot.eu</a>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">2. Purpose and Legal Basis of Processing</h2>
          <p class="text-[#E5E7EB] mb-4">We process your data only for the following purposes:</p>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-white/10 text-[#E5E7EB]">
              <thead>
                <tr class="bg-white/5">
                  <th class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3 text-left">Purpose</th>
                  <th class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3 text-left">Legal Basis (GDPR)</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Performance of sales contracts for shooting accessories</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Art. 6(1)(b)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-white/5">
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Account management in CoreShot Range Manager app</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Art. 6(1)(b)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Direct marketing (newsletter, promotions)</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Art. 6(1)(a) (consent)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-white/5">
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Traffic analysis in app and website (Google Analytics, Hotjar)</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Art. 6(1)(f) (legitimate interest)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Legal claims and defense</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Art. 6(1)(f)</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">3. What Data Do We Collect?</h2>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">When purchasing accessories:</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-[#E5E7EB]">
            <li>Name, surname, delivery address, email, phone</li>
            <li>Payment data (transferred to Stripe/PayU – we do not store card numbers)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">In CoreShot Range Manager app:</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-[#E5E7EB]">
            <li>Email address (login)</li>
            <li>Name, surname, shooting license number (optional)</li>
            <li>Shooting data: results, caliber, date, time</li>
            <li>Range location (GPS – only with consent)</li>
            <li>Scope photos (if you enable preview)</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 mt-6">On coreshot.eu website:</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-[#E5E7EB]">
            <li>Cookies (necessary, analytical, marketing)</li>
            <li>IP address, browser, visit time</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-white/10 text-[#E5E7EB]">
              <thead>
                <tr class="bg-white/5">
                  <th class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3 text-left">Type</th>
                  <th class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3 text-left">Purpose</th>
                  <th class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3 text-left">Storage Period</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Necessary</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Cart, login functionality</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Session</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-white/5">
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Analytical (Google Analytics)</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Visit statistics</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">up to 26 months</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Marketing (Meta Pixel)</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Social media advertising</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">up to 180 days</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[#E5E7EB] mt-4">
            <strong>You can disable cookies in your browser settings.</strong><br>
            We use a <strong>CMP (Consent Management Platform)</strong> compliant with TCF v2.2.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">5. Who Do We Share Data With?</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-[#E5E7EB]">
            <li><strong>IT service providers</strong>: AWS (Ireland), Vercel (USA – SCC)</li>
            <li><strong>Payments</strong>: Stripe, PayU</li>
            <li><strong>Logistics</strong>: DHL, InPost</li>
            <li><strong>Accounting office</strong></li>
            <li><strong>State authorities</strong> – only upon request (e.g., police, tax office)</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-[#E5E7EB] mt-4">
            <strong>All entities outside EEA have SCCs or are covered by Privacy Shield (if applicable).</strong>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">6. How Long Do We Store Data?</h2>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-white/10 text-[#E5E7EB]">
              <thead>
                <tr class="bg-white/5">
                  <th class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3 text-left">Data Type</th>
                  <th class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3 text-left">Storage Period</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Purchase data</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">5 years (accounting law)</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-white/5">
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">App account</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Until account deletion + 30 days</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Analytical data</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Max 26 months</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="bg-white/5">
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Marketing consent</td>
                  <td class="border border-white/10 px-4 py-3">Until withdrawal</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">7. Your Rights (GDPR)</h2>
          <p class="text-[#E5E7EB] mb-4">You have the right to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-[#E5E7EB]">
            <li><strong>Access</strong> your data</li>
            <li><strong>Rectification</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Erasure</strong> ("right to be forgotten")</li>
            <li><strong>Restriction of processing</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Data portability</strong> (JSON/CSV format)</li>
            <li><strong>Object</strong> (marketing, profiling)</li>
            <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> at any time</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-[#E5E7EB] mt-4">
            <strong>Submit request:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@coreshot.eu" class="text-[#E11D48] hover:underline">privacy@coreshot.eu</a><br>
            <strong>Response within 30 days.</strong>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">8. Security</h2>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-[#E5E7EB]">
            <li>TLS 1.3 encryption</li>
            <li>Data at rest: AES-256</li>
            <li>Regular penetration testing</li>
            <li>Password policy and 2FA for employees</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">9. Children's Data</h2>
          <p class="text-[#E5E7EB]">
            Our services <strong>are not intended for persons under 18 years of age</strong>.<br>
            If we learn that we are collecting data from a child – we will delete it immediately.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">10. Policy Changes</h2>
          <p class="text-[#E5E7EB]">
            We will notify you by email of <strong>significant changes</strong> (e.g., new processing purpose).<br>
            Minor updates – only the date at the top.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">11. Contact</h2>
          <p class="text-[#E5E7EB]">
            <strong>Data Protection Officer (DPO):</strong><br>
            <a href="mailto:iod@coreshot.eu" class="text-[#E11D48] hover:underline">iod@coreshot.eu</a>
          </p>
          <p class="text-[#E5E7EB] mt-4">
            <strong>Complaints to supervisory authority:</strong><br>
            Personal Data Protection Office (UODO)<br>
            ul. Stawki 2, 00-193 Warsaw, Poland
          </p>
        </section>

        <hr class="border-white/10 my-8">

        <p class="text-center text-xl text-white font-semibold">
          <strong>CoreShot™ – Precision. Technology. Reliability.</strong>
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .prose h3 {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .prose ul, .prose ol {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .prose li {
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }
</style>
